channel.title: Client of Dynasty. (HELP TO FIX RUN.BAT)
channel.description:
This is the code in "Run.Bat":
@ECHO OFF title Dynasty cd bin "C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_14\bin\java.exe" -Xmx512m com/dynasty/client pause
I don't know why but, when I click on Run, it says: The way of definite access is untraceable. It said this 2 times and I won't let me run it.
Anyone has an idea on how to fix this ?
Thanks.

item.title: Client of Dynasty. (HELP TO FIX RUN.BAT)
item.dc:creator: @cocoa cocoa
item.description:
@cocoa wrote:

What is your jdk version?

Replace this

"C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_14\bin\java.exe" -Xmx512m com/dynasty/client

with this except put your Jdk version where I put the ##

"C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_##\bin\java.exe" -Xmx512m com/dynasty/client
